/*
this is the template we are asking you to follow for the first step of learning express
up here you can write a sentence or two describing your app
*/

----------------------------------------------
all 'require' statements go in this top section
----------------------------------------------

----------------------------------------------
declare here any local variables you will need.
maybe a 'var DB = [];' or 'var playerState = true;'
also initializations like 'var app = express();'
----------------------------------------------

----------------------------------------------
all middleware come next (except for 404's0.  this is anything 'app.set' or 'app.use'.  
here you'll set view engines, use body parser, log traffic, ... 
anything that configures the app or helps manage it
----------------------------------------------

----------------------------------------------
all handlers go here.
anything with 'app.get' or 'app.post'
this section is the 'public facing logic' of your program.
The API if you want to use vocabulary
----------------------------------------------

----------------------------------------------
your '404' error message goes here.
because of the way middleware works in express,
this function will only be executed if no handlers were entered.
----------------------------------------------

----------------------------------------------
The final piece of your app will be the server connection
----------------------------------------------







